 Concluding remarks  
As the continuous spectrum in this situation is , our
theorem implies an analogue of Selberg's eigenvalue conjecture.
Note that our bound is stronger than result for 
from   who proved .  In general, our
method applies to  with  to give the bound  where  is the
number of fundamental domains which intersect a Siegel set containing
the fundamental domain constructed in  ; however, for 
, this bound is rather weak.  Finally, let us remark that our
theorem is indeed a consequence of the Ramanujan conjecture, which
asserts that all nontrivial automorphic representations come from
tempered representations.
